      "In mutual fund tracking, the most common hidden error is in the purchase date column. Excel stores dates as serial numbers, but if even one cell is accidentally entered as text -- perhaps by copy-pasting from a PDF or email -- every calculation that depends on that date will silently produce wrong results. FIFO matching, holding period calculation, and tax categorization can all fail without any visible error.",
