      "Every year, thousands of Indian mutual fund investors sit down in March to prepare their capital gains statement for ITR filing, and discover that their Excel records do not add up. The problem is almost never that they entered the wrong data -- it is that the formulas they built to process the data have a flaw that was invisible until reconciliation time.",
      "The most common flaw is the holding period calculation. Indian tax rules classify gains as short-term if the holding period is less than twelve months for equity funds (or less than twenty-four or thirty-six months for certain debt funds). The boundary date is critical. An off-by-one error in the date formula can misclassify a gain from LTCG to STCG or vice versa, changing the applicable tax rate significantly.",
